# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
#
# Pages applies a default "clean URL" rule that 308-redirects every
# /foo.html to /foo. That broke the Outlook add-in, because Outlook's
# add-in runtime doesn't follow redirects on SourceLocation /
# Commands.Url fetches — it just shows "We're sorry, we couldn't
# access Send to Claudia."
#
# The manifest itself was updated to point at the extensionless URLs,
# but classic Outlook caches the manifest aggressively. These rules
# REWRITE (status 200, not redirect) any straggler request for the
# old .html paths so even a cached/stale manifest still works.

/outlook-addin/commands.html  /outlook-addin/commands  200
/outlook-addin/taskpane.html  /outlook-addin/taskpane  200
